Add the GUI for duke.

The GUI allows user to input a text and receive
a response accordingly.

This is done using javafx. Be careful next time
when trying to update the UI.

Add a return statement for some function.

Because of how the code is written, an error
is thrown if none of the if statements are
satisfied.

This cause an error to be thrown even though
the command is valid. The return statement helps
to prevent the error part to be thrown.

Add some assertions.

The assertions check if there are any weird
anomalies. That is to say there must be
things we expect to be in a certain format,
or with a certain value must hold true.
Otherwise something is wrong with the
program for unknown reasons or
something is wrong with the user's device.

In the deadline and event command info,
the text used erroneously used \ instead of
/. For example, itshould be /by XXXX instead
of \by XXXX. I have changed this part so users
will be shown the correct input format.

Fix some bugs.

In the deletion of task, the task number
may not be valid. There may not be a check
used to ensure proper input. I have not added
a check to tell the user to reinput the correct
command.

Also, the remove command is also added.
This is to ensure people know about the
existence of a remove command.
